OL,3,CThe facts around UK maternity pay
OL,4,Cafter Badenoch suggests it's
OL,5,C'excessive'
OL,7,FMs Badenoch argued that businesses are
OL,8,Fbeing forced to close due to statutory
OL,9,Fmaternity pay obligations because "the
OL,10,Fburden of regulation is too high" -
OL,11,Fdespite companies being able to recoup
OL,12,Fmost of the payments from HMRC.
OL,14,FPut to her that she is saying
OL,15,Fmaternity pay is "excessive", Ms
OL,16,FBadenoch said: "I think it's gone too
OL,17,Ffar, too far the other way, in terms
OL,18,Fof general business regulation, we
OL,19,Fneed to allow businesses, especially
OL,20,Fsmall businesses, to make more of
OL,21,Ftheir own decisions.
