OL,3,CThe facts around UK maternity pay
OL,4,Cafter Badenoch suggests it's
OL,5,C'excessive'
OL,7,FAn employee must have worked with
OL,8,Ftheir employer continuously for a
OL,9,Fminimum of 26 weeks (approximately six
OL,10,Fmonths) and no less than 15 weeks
OL,11,Fbefore their due date. This means the
OL,12,Flatest an employee would be able to
OL,13,Fclaim statutory maternity pay after
OL,14,Fjoining a company would be 15 weeks
OL,15,Faway from giving birth (roughly five
OL,16,Fmonths pregnant).
