OL,3,CThe facts around UK maternity pay
OL,4,Cafter Badenoch suggests it's
OL,5,C'excessive'
OL,7,FAccording to the Organisation for
OL,8,FEconomic Co-operation and Development
OL,9,F(OECD), 19 weeks is the average amount
OL,10,Fof paid leave offered among OECD
OL,11,Fcountries. But countries such as
OL,12,FFrance, Germany, Austria, Turkey,
OL,13,FPoland, Croatia and others offer full
OL,14,Fpay for between 14-30 weeks.
OL,16,FNorway, for example, allows up to 59
OL,17,Fweeks paid maternity leave with new
OL,18,Fmums receiving 80% of their salary, or
OL,19,F49 weeks at full pay.
OL,21,FDo some companies offer more?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/18
