OL,3,CThe facts around UK maternity pay
OL,4,Cafter Badenoch suggests it's
OL,5,C'excessive'
OL,7,FPointing this out, Joeli Brearley,
OL,8,Ffounder of Pregnant Then Screwed,
OL,9,Fsaid: "It is absolute nonsense to
OL,10,Fsuggest that businesses are closing
OL,11,Fbecause of statutory maternity pay."
OL,13,FShe said Badenoch's comments were "yet
OL,14,Fanother example of dog-whistle
OL,15,Fpolitics", adding: "Statutory
OL,16,Fmaternity pay is absolutely vital.
OL,17,FMost families need two incomes to
OL,18,Fsurvive, and so without SMP, women
OL,19,Fwould be forced to return to work
OL,20,Falmost immediately after giving birth."
